body:
This bug first appears in 3.17.0 (tested with PHAR) and seems to be in all versions up to 4.3.1. Didn't check master.

I couldn't replicate it with psaml.dev, so I created the following minimal project ([test.tar.gz](https://github.com/vimeo/psalm/files/5672247/test.tar.gz)) consisting of two files:

src/X.php
```php
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Foo;

final class X
{
    /**
     * @var \SplObjectStorage
     */
    private $seen;

    /**
     * @var int
     */
    private $failures;

    public function __construct()
    {
        $this->seen = new \SplObjectStorage();
        $this->failures = 0;
    }

    public function validate(array $expected, int $argument, int $distance = 1): void
    {
        // The bug appears only when the following assignments are within
        // finally block and in this specific order.
        try {
        } finally {
            $this->failures = 0;
            $this->seen = new \SplObjectStorage();
        }
    }
}

// vim: syntax=php sw=4 ts=4 et:
```

and  psalm.xml

```xml
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<psalm
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xmlns="https://getpsalm.org/schema/config"
    xsi:schemaLocation="https://getpsalm.org/schema/config vendor/vimeo/psalm/config.xsd"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
    rememberPropertyAssignmentsAfterCall="false"
>
    <projectFiles>
        <directory name="src" />
    </projectFiles>
</psalm>
```

Running psalm (PHAR, any version between 3.17.0 and 4.3.1 inclusive) yields the following error

